skills.prompt:
Create a strategic canvas for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Cover vision, goals, audience, positioning, business model, pricing considerations, launch plan, risks, assumptions, and next actions. Keep the result practical and decision-ready.

Create a custom review checklist for this work.

Input: {{input}}

Tailor the checklist to the work type, include pass/fail criteria, common risks, and a concise final review procedure.

Help debug likely context or memory issues for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Identify loaded context signals, possible stale or conflicting assumptions, what to verify, and how to proceed without compounding wrong context.

Plan and execute an intelligent batch rename workflow.

Input: {{input}}

Inspect target files before renaming, infer useful names from contents, use a clear naming convention such as YYYY-MM-DD_description_type when appropriate, and summarize every proposed or completed rename.

Find duplicate and near-duplicate files for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Compare names, sizes, hashes, and content where useful. Show candidates, confidence, and recommended action. Do not delete anything without explicit approval.

Create a logical folder structure for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Inspect the current files, propose a structure, move or organize only when allowed, avoid active or sensitive files unless requested, and summarize what went where.

Archive stale files for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Identify stale files using the requested age or access criteria, explicitly protect active paths, show the archive plan, and avoid destructive deletion unless separately approved.

Generate a reusable template from completed examples.

Input: {{input}}

Identify the recurring structure, required sections, optional sections, tone, placeholders, and quality checks. Produce a clean blank template.

Search and extract relevant passages for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Search across the target documents, extract useful passages, preserve source file and page or location when available, and compile the findings into a single organized brief.

Convert files for this request.

Input: {{input}}

Preserve formatting, headings, bullets, filenames, and folder structure where possible. Report unsupported files and verify converted outputs before finishing.

Run a storage size audit.

Input: {{input}}

Find the largest files, estimate what can be archived or removed based on age and context, and show recommendations without deleting anything.

Triage email and save a summary.

Input: {{input}}

Categorize messages into urgent, needs response, FYI, and low priority. Draft routine replies but do not send without approval. Save or prepare a dated summary when Drive access is available.

Prepare meeting briefs.

Input: {{input}}

Review the requested calendar window, identify meetings and attendees, gather useful context when available, and create concise prep briefs with goals, background, risks, and questions.

Extract Slack action items.

Input: {{input}}

Scan the requested Slack scope, find action items directed at the user, group them by channel or project, rank urgency, and save or summarize the task list.

Analyze Drive or spreadsheet data and create a concise slide narrative.

Input: {{input}}

Find the top insights, build clear charts when useful, and prepare a short deck with recommendations and source notes.

Resolve an email chain.

Input: {{input}}

Find or review the thread, summarize decisions, open issues, owners, and deadlines, then draft a follow-up that moves the conversation forward. Do not send without approval.

Build a multi-source report.

Input: {{input}}

Pull together the requested sources, reconcile conflicts, cite where information came from, and produce a formatted report with summary, details, and next actions.

Process meeting notes for distribution.

Input: {{input}}

Extract action items with owners and deadlines, draft concise follow-ups for each person, and show drafts before sending.

Run a cross-platform search.

Input: {{input}}

Search the requested connected sources, organize results by source, deduplicate overlaps, and compile a useful project dossier.

Turn a voice transcript into a polished draft.

Input: {{input}}

Preserve the user's natural voice, add structure, clarify ideas, remove filler, and make the result publication-ready.

Process a meeting transcript into structured notes.

Input: {{input}}

Extract decisions, action items with owners and deadlines, open questions, and key points. Format the result as clear markdown.

Create an executive research brief.

Input: {{input}}

Synthesize the sources, flag conflicting viewpoints, recommend actions, and include source notes. Keep it concise and executive-ready.

Customize a proposal.

Input: {{input}}

Use the template structure, tailor every section to the client brief, preserve a professional tone, and call out assumptions or missing client details.

Summarize a contract in plain English.

Input: {{input}}

Identify key terms, deadlines, renewal clauses, liability caps, unusual provisions, and practical questions. This is a first-pass summary, not legal advice.

Write a narrative from spreadsheet data.

Input: {{input}}

Identify top trends, anomalies, and recommended actions. Include important numbers and explain what they mean for a non-technical audience.

Repurpose content across channels.

Input: {{input}}

Create channel-specific versions while preserving the core message. Include options for short posts, LinkedIn, captions, newsletter teaser, and any requested formats.

Assemble a weekly newsletter.

Input: {{input}}

Review available drafts, pick the strongest items, write an intro, teasers, transitions, and sign-off, then produce a polished newsletter draft.

Run or prepare a daily inbox-zero routine.

Input: {{input}}

Categorize unread emails, draft routine responses, flag urgent items, and save a summary. If scheduling is requested, use the app's scheduling flow and confirm before external side effects.

Run or prepare a weekly file cleanup workflow.

Input: {{input}}

Sort target folders by type and project, protect important paths, identify stale files, and confirm before deleting anything.

Create a Monday planning brief.

Input: {{input}}

Review the requested week, calendar, prep materials, and open items when available. Produce priorities, deadlines, risks, and next actions.

Organize monthly financial records.

Input: {{input}}

Extract vendor, amount, date, and category from receipts or statements when available, build a categorized expense table, and flag missing or uncertain fields.

Run a competitive scan.

Input: {{input}}

Check the requested competitors for recent news, pricing changes, launches, hiring signals, and material differences from prior scans. Save a concise intelligence brief.

Create an end-of-day work log.

Input: {{input}}

Review available context, files changed or created when accessible, and current tasks. Summarize accomplishments, in-progress work, blockers, and tomorrow's priorities.
